story==\nDemocratic Front party was founded by [[\u017deljko Kom\u0161i\u0107]], Croatian Member of Presidency of Bosnia and Herzegovina who left the [[Social Democratic Party of Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in July 2012.\n\n==Electoral results==\n===Presidency elections===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ [[Presidency of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n! Election year\n! #\n! Candidate\n! Representing\n! Votes\n! %\n! Elected?\n|-\n!rowspan=2| [[2014 Bosnian general election|2014]]\n|3rd\n|''[[Emir Suljagi\u0107]]''\n| [[Bosniaks]]\n|''114,334''\n|''15.2%''\n|{{no}}\n|-\n|4th\n|''Anto Popovi\u0107''\n| [[Croats]]\n|''7,179''\n|''2.9%''\n|{{no}}\n|-\n! [[2018 Bosnian general election|2018]]\n|1st\n|''[[\u017deljko Kom\u0161i\u0107]]''\n| [[Croats]]\n| ''225,500''\n| ''52.6%''\n|{{yes}}\n|}\n\n===Parliamentary elections===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ [[Parliamentary Assembly of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n! Year\n! #\n! Popular vote\n! [[House of Representatives of Bosnia and Herzegovina|HoR]]\n! Seat change\n! [[House of Peoples of Bosnia and Herzegovina|HoP]]\n! Seat change\n! Government\n|-\n!rowspan=2|[[2014 Bosnian general election|2014]]\n|rowspan=2|4th\n|rowspan=2|150,767\n|rowspan=2|{{Composition bar|5|42|hex=#FF6600}}\n|rowspan=2|{{steady}}\n|rowspan=2|{{Composition bar|1|15|hex=#FF6600}}\n|rowspan=2|{{steady}}\n|{{yes|government (until 2015)}}\n|-\n|{{no|opposition (from 2015)}}\n|-\n! [[2018 Bosnian general election|2018]]\n|6th\n|96,180\n| {{Composition bar|3|42|hex=#FF6600}}\n| {{decrease}} 2\n| {{Composition bar|1|15|hex=#FF6600}}\n| {{steady}}\n| {{yes|government}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Bosnian political parties}}\n\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Bosnian nationalism]]\n[[Category:Civic nationalism]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Social democratic parties in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Pro-European political parties in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\