{"title_page": "Jaan Tomp (journalist)", "text_new": "'''Jaan Tomp''' (13 May 1882 \u2013 1943) was an Estonian journalist. He was born in Uue-V\u00f5idu vald, [[Viljandi County]]. From 1905\u20131908 he worked for ''[[Kodumaa]]'', followed by ''[[Kodumaa H\u00e4\u00e4l]]'', ''[[Maa (newspaper)|Maa]]'', ''[[Meie Kodu]]'' and ''[[Meie Kodumaa]]''.<ref>{{cite book|title=Sitzungsberichte der Gelehrten Estnischen Gesellschaft|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LnIoAQAAMAAJ|year=1988|publisher=K. Mattiesen'i tr\u00fckk|language=Estonian|page=212}}</ref>\nIn 1919-1920 he was chairman of the [[Estonian Journalists' Union]], and was an honorary member from 1934.\nFrom 1918 until 1937 he was an editor of ''[[Vaba Maa]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tomp, Jaan}}\n[[Category:1882 births]]\n[[Category:1943 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Viljandi County]]\n[[Category:People from the Governorate of Livonia]]\n[[Category:Estonian journalists]]\n[[Category:Estonian non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Estonian writers]]\n[[Category:Estonian male writers]]\n\n\n{{Estonia-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Jaan Tomp''' (13 May 1882 \u2013 1943) was an Estonian journalist. He was born in Uue-V\u00f5idu vald, [[Viljandi County]]. From 1905\u20131908 he worked for ''[[Kodumaa]]'', followed by ''[[Kodumaa H\u00e4\u00e4l]]'', ''[[Maa (newspaper)|Maa]]'', ''[[Meie Kodu]]'' and ''[[Meie Kodumaa]]''.<ref>{{cite book|title=Sitzungsberichte der Gelehrten Estnischen Gesellschaft|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LnIoAQAAMAAJ|year=1988|publisher=K. Mattiesen'i tr\u00fckk|language=Estonian|page=212}}</ref>\nIn 1919-1920 he was chairman of the [[Estonian Journalists' Union]], and was an honorary member from 1934.\nFrom 1918 until 1937 he was an editor of ''[[Vaba Maa]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tomp, Jaan}}\n[[Category:1882 births]]\n[[Category:1943 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Viljandi County]]\n[[Categ