{"title_page": "Richard Pare", "text_new": "'''Richard Pare''' (born 20 February 1948 in [[Portsmouth]], England) is an English photographer known for his work documenting [[Stalinist architecture|Soviet]] [[modernist architecture]]. He was born in [[Portsmouth]], England, on 20 January 1948. He studied graphic design and photography at Winchester and [[Ravensbourne (college)|Ravensbourne College of Art]] before attending the [[Art Institute of Chicago]]. He received a [[Master of Fine Arts]] from Chicago in 1973. He was the founding curator of the Photography Collection of the [[Canadian Centre for Architecture]]. \n\nRichard Pare curated the exhibition \"[https://www.cca.qc.ca/en/events/2795/photography-and-architecture-18391939 Photography and Architecture: 1839\u20131939]\" at the [[Canadian Centre for Architecture]] in 1982. Exhibitions of his photographs include \"[https://www.moma.org/calendar/exhibitions/47 Lost Vanguard: Soviet Modernist Architecture, 1922\u201332]\" (2007) and \"[https://www.moma.org/calendar/exhibitions/1297 Le Corbusier: An Atlas of Modern Landscapes]\" at the [[Museum of Modern Art]] (2013).\n\n==Selected Publications==\n* Richard Pare (1982). ''Photography and Architecture, 1839-1939''. Montr\u00e9al: [[Canadian Centre for Architecture]]; [New York]: Callaway Editions.\n* Richard Pare (1996). ''The Colours of Light: Tadao Ando Architecture''. London: [[Phaidon Press|Phaidon]].\n* Richard Pare (2007). ''[https://www.moma.org/documents/moma_catalogue_47_300324595.pdf The Lost Vanguard: Russian Modernist Architecture 1922-1932]''. New York: The Monacelli Press.\n* Richard Pare and [[Jean-Louis Cohen]] (2018). ''Le Corbusier: The Built Work''. New York: The Monacelli Press.\n* Richard Pare (2018). ''Tadao Ando: The Colours of Light, Volume 1''. London: [[Phaidon Press|Phaidon]]. (2nd edition)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Russian avant-garde]]\n* [[List of photographers]]\n\n==References==\n* {{ cite journal | author=Richard Anderson | title=Taking Stock: Documenting Russia's Modern Heritage  | url=http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/future_anterior/v005/5.1.anderson.pdf | journal=[[Future Anterior]] | year=2008 | volume=5 | issue=1 | id= {{ISSN|1549-9715}} (print), {{ISSN|1934-6026}} (online) }} See also other articles from the [http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/future_anterior/toc/fta.5.1.html same issue] illustrated by Pare\n\n== External links ==\n* {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080820215601/http://www.avangard-ru.org/pdf/press/RussianAvantgarde_RG_eng.9062.pdf |date=August 20, 2008 |title=Russian Avant-garde in New York}}\n* {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080325174157/http://moma.org/exhibitions/exhibitions.php?id=5138 |date=March 25, 2008 |title=Lost Vanguard:Soviet Modernist Architecture, 1922\u201332 Photographs by Richard Pare}}\n* [http://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2008/03/pare-m06.html An interview with Richard Pare, co-author and photographer of The Lost Vanguard: Russian Modernist Architecture, 1922-1932] with Tim Tower on the ''[[World Socialist Web Site]]''\n* [https://www.whitespacegallery.co.uk/artist/richard-pare/ Bio and photographs at the White Space Gallery, London]\n* [https://www.cca.qc.ca/en/search?query=richard%20pare&filters=%7B%22forms_collection_library_bookstore%22%3A%5B%22photographs%22%5D%7D Richard Pare, photographs], [[Canadian Centre for Architecture]] ([https://www.cca.qc.ca/en/search?query=richard%20pare&filters=%7B%22forms_collection_library_bookstore%22%3A%5B%22photographs%22%5D%7D&img_filter=1 digitized items])\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pare, Richard}}\n[[Category:English photographers]]\n[[Category:Architectural photographers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Guggenheim Fellows]]\n\n\n{{UK-photographer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Richard Pare''' (born 20 February 1948 in [[Portsmouth]], England) is an English photographer known for his work documenting [[Stalinist architecture|Soviet]] [[modernist architecture]]. He was born in [[Portsmouth]], England, on 20 January 1948. He studied graphic design and photography at Winchester and [[Ravensbourne (college)|Ravensbourne College of Art]] before attending the [[Art Institute of Chicago]]. He received a [[Master of Fine Arts]] from Chicago in 1973. He was the founding curator of the Photography Collection of the [[Canadian Centre for Architecture]]. \n\nRichard Pare curated the exhibition \"[https://www.cca.qc.ca/en/events/2795/photography-and-architecture-18391939 Photography and Architecture: 1839\u20131939]\" at the [[Canadian Centre for Architecture]] in 1982. Exhibitions of his photographs include \"[https://www.moma.org/calendar/exhibitions/47 Lost Vanguard: Soviet Modernist Architecture, 1922\u201332]\" (2007) and \"[https://www.moma.org/calendar/exhibitions/1297 Le Corbusier: An Atlas of Modern Landscapes]\" at the [[Museum of Modern Art]] (2013).\n\n==Selected Publications==\n* Richard Pare (1982). ''Photography and Architecture, 1839-1939''. Montr\u00e9al: [[Canadian Centre for Architecture]]; [New York]: Callaway Editions.\n* Richard Pare (1996). ''The Colours of Light: Tadao Ando Architecture''. London: [[Phaidon Press|Phaidon]].\n* Richard Pare (2007). ''[https://www.moma.org/documents/moma_catalogue_47_300324595.pdf The Lost Vanguard: Russian Modernist Architecture 1922-1932]''. New York: The Monacelli Press.\n* Richard Pare and [[Jean-Louis Cohen]] (2018). ''Le Corbusier: The Built Work''. New York: The Monacelli Press.\n* Richard Pare (2018). ''Tadao Ando: The Colours of Light, Volume 1''. London: [[Phaidon Press|Phaidon]]. (2nd edition)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Russian avant-garde]]\n* [[List of photographers]]\n\n==References==\n* {{ cite journal | author=Richard Anderson | title=Taking Stock: Documenting Russia's Modern Heritage  | url=http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/future_anterior/v005/5.1.anderson.pdf | journal=[[Future Anterior]] | year=2008 | volume=5 | issue=1 | id= {{ISSN|1549-9715}} (print), {{ISS